text: Gravity Orange isn't anything new. While its colors and animations may hold the attention of users, eventually most will give up out of frustration or boredom, whichever comes first.
title: Gravity Orange

text: Triples isn't a memorable game, there really isn't too much of a point to it. Its yet another puzzle type game that fails to separate itself from the rest of the puzzle games on the market.
title: Triples

text: Little Caves is a maze game. Nothing new, pretty much pac man without the ghosts and worse animations. This app is one of a million and fails to stand out in any way.
title: Little Caves

text: Some people really seem to love this game. It just didn't do it for me. Armadillos? I can do without them. Honestly, maybe I would have liked the game more if the armadillo had a fun name. Boring.

text: Vampire Village is a basic game. Basic animations, basic characters, basic plots. Certainly not worth downloading, and certainly not worth playing.
title: Vampire Village

text: That little cartoon monster with the aw shucks" look on his face is really cute which is why it pains me to say I don't recommend the game. I'm pretty hard to please with a mobile game though. So maybe take it with a grain of salt when I say the game is unmemorable and not worth your time."

text: Blink Box uses bright colors and flashing lights to draw and keep your attention. It is easy to pass time with and is entertaining, but there isn't much to it.
title: Blink Blox

text: I don't understand why people like this game. You have to help a frog move limb by limb to catch food. There isn't much of a goal in the game and it isn't anything you can't find in another app.
title: Ancient Frog

text: As a grammar fanatic, I'm a little irked by the fact that sapphire" is misspelled. The cartoon character you play in this game is a little red devil and he's trying to capture the safires (essentially the blue diamonds that we call sapphires). It's an OK game."
title: Safire

text: Well, you'll be hard-pressed to find a game that comes more highly recommended! Friends of mine love this game and you will two. It's a puzzler, that's for sure.
title: Wayse

text: Similar to bejewelled and crushing blocks, this game asks you to select groups of the same fruit that are then removed from the screen. It's a fairly mindless, repetitive game, but good for moments when you're overworked or stressed out and want to zone out for a bit.
title: Fruit Fling

text: Others who've played High Low Spinner before me must've really liked it. I know i've given it a lower score than most. But I just found it really dull. It's poorly packaged, looks like no fun at all and really wasn't much fun for me. I won't play again.
title: High Low Spinner

text: Mazonaut provides a unique setting with good animations. While it remains a typical adventure type game, it does provide some variation on objectives that many users will enjoy.
title: Mazonaut

text: Little Acorns is a typical adventure type game. You help a squirrel gather as many acorns as you can over a given amount of time, with some obstacles along the way.
title: Little Acorns

text: Droid Getaway is another adventure style game, and in this case you're helping a robot  defeat enemies, trying to reach the end of the level without dying. It isn't all that special, but is entertaining.
title: Droid Getaway

text: If you're like me, you've been fascinated with the idea of cracking safes since Charlize Theron did it in that movie, The Italian Job. She made it look so cool! That's why I was immediately interested in this game and I found it tons of fun.
title: Crack That Vault

text: Let's get water to those farmers! They're in desperate need of some H2O, and it's your job when you play this game to get water to the crops that need it. You'll move pipes, answer puzzles and save the day! Lots of fun.
title: Drip

text: Slide Road is more unique than many apps on the market. While you have one objective for the entire game, you reach your objective not by defeating opponents, but by driving and avoiding obstacles. Definitely entertaining though.
title: Slide Road

text: Pathway is a simple app that anybody could have created with a few hours of work and some basic coding skills. While it may appeal to people who like logic-based games, this app isn't for everyone, especially kids and teens.
title: Pathway Game

text: in Stash Dash players help a squirrel stash away all kinds of acorns, nuts, and seeds for the oncoming winter. Its a race against the clock type of game that isn't really all that special, though it is certainly entertaining until you get frustrated enough to quit!
title: Stash Dash

text: Pack your bags and a copy of the Illiad! It's time to set off on a journey, one with game-play and puzzle-solving. I only hope it's not a quixotic quest and that you find what you're looking for! Good luck!
title: The Quest

text: Knock It provides the standard app experience. Players have one goal, and the objective doesn't change as you play the game. It might be good for bragging rights, but actually isn't all that entertaining.
title: Knock It

text: Be careful or you'll run smack into Zombie Granny! This is a fun game, captivating for mobile gamers of all ages who love a good zombie. Definitely check it out!
title: Zombie Granny

text: Glow Worm is an interesting app where you protect bacteria from their surrounding environments. While not necessarily scientifically correct, it is much more complex than many other apps out there, and that sets it apart.
title: Glow Worm

text: In deflection, the players are supposed to avoid obstacles, guiding a ball to the goal. It is different from other puzzle type games in that you're not just solving puzzles, but rather making your own way around the obstacles.
title: Deflection

text: What's the story in this game again? See, I can't even remember. I'm pretty sure it wasn't the worst mobile game I've ever played. Just don't care to play it again.
title: Animal Eye

text: Voodoo Friends focuses around stabbing voodoo dolls with needles. While this may be entertaining in the short term, in the long term there isn't much to it.
title: Voodoo Friends

text: Odum isn't anything special. You watch a smiley face bounce up and down on the screen and avoid obstacles. Its nothing new, and nothing that you can't find in another app.
title: Odum

text: Fighting bugs? No thanks. I don't think I'm the only person who didn't really enjoy this game very much; others rated it worse than I did. It's just boring. The people marketing the game didn't do much to make it look fun, either!

text: Faaaalling Balls! Beware the falling balls! You have to avoid collision with the balls in this game to win it. It's kind of a cross between Pac-Man and Angry Birds; you'll enjoy it!

text: In Drop the Nut, users control a box, trying to slide it back and forth to catch coconuts falling from a trees. It certainly isn't anything players haven't seen before.

text: Red Block Puzzle is the typical traffic jam reiteration. The developers didn't add anything to the game, they just changed the colors and shapes and published it hoping to draw attention.
title: Red Block Puzzle

text: Blah. Vague and boring, this game is. I was totally uninspired by the description and can tell you I wouldn't waste my time on it. This game needs something unique to make it worth playing.
title: Rainbow Ball Rush

text: Take it or leave it. I'm not really sure what the game's about. It's there if you're truly bored. I don't think I'd waste my time. The name and the icon aren't really descriptive or fun.... I like more pizzazz.
title: The Pyramid

text: This is a fun game that requires you to shift portions of the slide to direct the timber logs to the desired endpoint. It's a challenging game but I'd recommend it to anyone who's ever ridden the log flume at Dorney Park -- it reminds me a lot of that amusement park ride!
title: Timber Slide

text: Hoist up the sails and let's set off for a wonderful trip to Lambi Islands! This island is home to so-ugly-they're-cute monsters and magical fun that'll keep you -- or the five-year-old who steals your phone at family dinners -- entralled. Have fun!
title: Lambi Islands

text: Shoot off into space, and wonder quickly if you should give up and go home. Eh. This game's alright but it's nothing amazing. Can I have back the 20 minutes I spent playing?
title: Space Dust

text: Agent Duck is a very well-developed game. Its animations and objectives will keep players entertained for hours on end. Despite this, it really seems childish due to the characters.
title: Agent Duck

text: This game intrigued me from the minute I saw its name. I love a good Victorian setting and grand old houses. The puzzles and games you play inside this game are captivating and fun. Try it out!
title: Victorian Mysteries

text: Probably one of the highest rated games and for good reason! Hank Hazard is adorable, he's memorable and his challenges are fun to get through. You'll like this game if you like games like Angry Birds.
title: Hank Hazard

text: Castle Escape is the typical mystery type app. It focuses mainly on puzzles and solving them in order to escape a pyramid, which raises the question why is it castle escape and not pyramid escape?
title: Castle Escape

text: Rusty Robots features -- you guessed it! -- some rusty robots. These rusty mechanical tin buckets are missing parts. See if you can put them all the way back together again! It's pretty fun.
title: Rusty Robots

text: In Hoot, players try to knock owls off of their perches. This app is not a good one for kids, as it teaches them that it is okay to be cruel to animals. I would not recommend this app!

text: I highly recommend this game! It's a bit mysterious and totally fun. I loved it from the second I read the description; I just knew I'd love it. If you like creepy and mysterious, you'll like this!

text: Pastry Pig features a pig that you help to hoard pastries. It glorifies sweet treats, and probably isn't a good app for younger, impressionable players who still need guidance in eating healthy. Other than that, it is a fun game.

text: Jump out focuses on using smooth animations to draw its users in. It reminds me a lot of other apps, but is surprisingly better than most of the apps on the market.
title: Jump Out

text: Let Me Out also uses more cartoon-like animation to differentiate itself from many apps on the market. However, the plot and game style are typical of other apps.
title: Let Me Out

text: Eh, what can I say? No, seriously, what can I say? The game's got a boring name and its little cartoony icon doesn't tell you anything about it. It's a soda-pop-without-fizz kind of game. Don't bother!

text: Shape star would probably be good for a younger audience. Its puzzles aren't all that complicated, and the bright colors and shapes would likely keep a toddler interested, not necessarily a teenager or adult.
title: Shape Star

text: This game is pretty unmemorable. I wouldn't recommend it simply because I don't remember it, and if it's not memorable, it's not worth spending your time on, right? Skip it.
title: Tanglers

text: While Crate is entertaining, there is no point to the game. You select the matching blocks and earn points. In the end it isn't anything all that special.
title: Crate

text: In Nuts Physics, players use basic laws of motion to help a squirrel capture its acorns and various foods. This might be entertaining for all of twenty minutes before uninstalled.

text: Puzzle-lovers, step right up! This is a game made just for you! Tons of puzzles, tons of fun. If you don't play this game, you're truly missing out. I recommend it to anyone who loves puzzles.

text: Pipe Fiction is definitely an entertaining game. Players help drops of water navigate through pipes to their targets, combining puzzle type games with adventure type games to make a satisfyingly distinct user experience. Its hard to come across an app like this, one that doesn't really have a predecessor!

text: I know others who've played this game liked it more than me. Can't really tell you why, but I just wasn't that into it. I'd recommend other games before this one.

text: Jet Worm juxtaposes a worm and a jet pack into an adventure style game that is sure to keep kids and adults entertained. Its fun characters, settings, and animations make the game stand out!

text: Flexy Frogs reminds me of the original frogger. Players help a group of frogs reunite at one location. In the end it provides minimal entertainment.

text: I'm happy to tell you that Gum Drop is an exciting game! It came recommended by a few friends and I enjoyed my time with it. You'll have fun, I promise you. Just download and give it a try.

text: So this game's all about saving the planet, right? People don't seem to want to play games that are eco-conscious; maybe the guilt of leaving on lights and leaving the water running while brushing their teeth is too much to handle and they don't want to be reminded of it by playing such a game? It's an OK game.

text: I really don't even know what Cub and Mug are trying to do. They're kind of cute little figures but they've got stupid names. I wouldn't waste my time with the game.

text: Mice Run allows players to control a mouse, facing obstacles and solving puzzles in order to get to the end of the game. Entertaining in the short term, but there is no long term reward to playing this game.

text: Droppix tries to draw its players in with bright colors, however the animation is pretty basic and it is yet another puzzle type game. Can't recommend it.

text: While waste is the typical turn the pipes before the water (or monster waste in this case) comes through type game, it stands out from other apps in its bright colors and animations.

text: I'm going to be honest, here: There's nothing truly earth-shattering about this game. But if you enjoy trying to find your way through mazes real and virtual, you'll enjoy playing this game. I love it.

text: Have you ever played Whack-a-Mole at Chuck E. Cheeze's and felt like it was a game sent straight from hell, or maybe even created by the same guys who invented water torture? Yeah, that's exactly how I felt with this game." You've gotta turn the lights off as soon as they come on. You're timed. It's terrible. Annoying. Stressful. No fun!"

text: This game challenges you to get to the green squares without failure. If you mess up, it punishes you. I don't really like games that penalize you, but if that doesn't bother you, check it out!

text: Lights Off tries to be a serious game, but since it's restricted to mobile platforms, it doesn't do all that much. The ironic part is that your phone's backlight is practically always on, so there's not much Lights off" going on here. "
title: Lights Off

text: Victorian Mysteries is a murder-mystery game. You'll play through it once and realize there's not much replayability, and the mystery wasn't even that great.
title: Victorian Mysteries

text: An interesting physics based game with an owl theme. A distracting way to pass time. Seems similar to Angry Birds and other related applications.
title: Hoot

text: Safire is a platforming game about a guy named Safire. You'll do all sorts of platforming things like run, jump, and stomp on platforms. You might do well just to stick with Mario though.
title: Safire

text: In this game you are on a fantastical journey to release a dragon from a book. It is a unique premise and is definitely entertaining. Original and fun.
title: Let Me Out

text: The Pyramid is a puzzle game where you'll go through pyramid-shaped puzzles across multiple levels. It gets pretty old really fast, and it tries to be some new age Rubik's Cube.
title: The Pyramid

text: In this game you are two rabbits trying to steal things. Feels a little odd and trite, but is still fun nonetheless because it is a little bit mindless.
title: Robber Rabbits

text: The Quest is an RPG where you play some faceless avatar in the pursuit of traditional RPG loot. There's not much here, and the only quest you'll try is to uninstall this game.
title: The Quest

text: High Low Spinner is a game where you have to guess a number, and either move it up or down to reach the target number as close as possible. It's kinda dull, since that's all there is to it.
title: High Low Spinner

text: Lambi Islands is a strange game about a set of islands with weird, awkward creatures. You'll be confused on what your goal is to do, and mission objectives aren't clearly defined. Stay away from this one.
title: Lambi Islands

text: Another game involving squirrels and acorns. This is similar to a lot of other physics games, so if you don't like physics games or squirrels, I wouldn't really try this out.
title: Nuts Physics

text: A fun puzzle game that involved flipping disks. It is colorful and challenging and good for people who are looking for something a little less mindless.
title: All Out

text: Nothing beats fighting robots. Try to escape while avoiding obstacles and other droids. This game is fun and entertaining. It is simple and similar to other obstacle escape apps.
title: Droid Getaway

text: Cub and Mag is a game about two shapes that are best friends, and you're goal is to help them find one another. It's a bit strange that they get separated so easily, but it's an alright game.
title: Cub And Mag

text: The game was about creating a slide to move logs from the top to the bottom. It's sorta straightforward, but even though it may be interesting at first, it gets old fairly quickly.
title: Timber Slide

text: This is an entertaining game with simple graphics and fun little yellow ball-guy. I would recommend it for someone looking to pass some spare time.
title: Odum

text: This is one of many games out there about squirrels who are running and collecting things. Nothing really sticks out about it compared to other apps, but is still fun.
title: Stash Dash

text: In this game you're helping out beavers and making sure their television doesn't go away. This game is mindless and entertaining and isn't too strenuous.
title: Save My Telly

text: Fruit Fling is a lot like Bubble Bash; you have different fruits queued up and you try and shoot them at a descending row of other fruits to form combos. Nothing seems too special, and it seems like a terrible spin-off from Fruit Ninja.
title: Fruit Fling

text: Moovin Up is a game about moving your cow from one pasture to another just so it doesn't starve to death. It's a weird premise, considering cows will pretty much go towards any patch of grass without needing to be told where to go. If it was about sheep and water... maybe, but this game isn't that great.
title: Moovin Up

text: Armadillo, like it's name suggests, is about an armadillo. You'll roll around in an adventure-esque game, but the graphics seem too terrible even by mobile standards.
title: Armadillo

text: Bug Battles is a game about exterminating bugs. You'll set out traps and hope that you kill all of the bugs before they reach a destination. Pretty much a tower defense game with poorly rendered versions of your worst nightmares.
title: Bug Battles

text: In this game you're a cute blocky bear, which is enough to make you want to play. It is an interesting arcade-like game. It is fun even if it isn't super groundbreaking.
title: Block Bear

text: This is a fun, minimalist, and entertaining puzzle game. All you need to focus on is the squares and the task at hand. It's an elegant and simple little game.
title: Pathway Game

text: In this game you're on a tropical island trying to get coconuts off of their trees. It's an interesting premise. I would definitely give it a try.
title: Drop The Nut

text: This is a simple pattern based shape and physics game. It is fun and original. If you're looking for something different I would play this one.
title: Deflection

text: Box Monsters is about these monsters... in the form of boxes. There's not much here in terms of content, so you can probably skip this one. You can, however, use it to just have this boxy icon just because.
title: Box Monsters

text: Crack That Vault gives you an interesting premise: you're framed, and the only thing to secure your innocence is behind a locked vault... which you have to crack. Irony aside, it's a decent puzzle game that kinda tries to be a bit serious.
title: Crack That Vault

text: This is a fun and elegant puzzle game. It manages to be challenging without being overly complex. For those who like puzzles and challenges, I would recommend trying it out.
title: Triples

text: Wayse is a puzzle game about coloring all of the blocks on the board without overlapping with a previous mood. It's rather interesting, but it's a lot like a slower paced Centipede.
title: Wayse

text: In this game you are trying to accomplish a task using voodoo dolls. A little weird at first, it's fun and unique and definitely entertaining.
title: Voodoo Friends

text: Kinopian is a Bubble Pop clone; you'll have different elements queued up, and you'll have to shoot it at descending elements to form combos. You're probably better off staying with the original since it's free, but if you want a new skin of the game, by all means get this game.
title: Kinopian

text: In this game you're a pig who runs a bakery. Combines elements of puzzle and physics games. It is entertaining and I would recommend this to others.
title: Pastry Pig

text: In this game you are a little jumping bug. Similar to a lot of other physics based jumping games. If you like those kinds of games I would try this one.
title: Jump Out

text: Mazes is, well, about mazes. You're given new sets of mazes to complete daily, and as you complete more mazes, the difficulty ramps up. Seems like there's a huge learning curve as the difficulty scales higher though, so if you like mazes, get the game, and if not, there's nothing much to see.
title: Mazes

text: This application is a puzzle game featuring little vampires. It is entertaining and a good way to pass time when you have a free moment to spare.
title: Vampire Village

text: This game involves matching and fitting shapes. It seems a little simple, so I would be more likely to recommend this to younger users rather than older.
title: Shape Star

text: This game is reminiscent of Temple Run and is entertaining and features a little bit of everything. There's adventure and faced paced game play.
title: Castle Escape

text: Zombie Granny is a Plants vs. Zombie styled game, but instead of trying to put granny down, you're trying to guide her to be less... zombie-ish. It's an alright game for a mobile game, but the graphics are a bit awful.
title: Zombie Granny

text: In this game you are an experimental mouse looking to escape from the prison of a scientific lab. Fun and entertaining with a unique premise.
title: Mice Run

text: Evil Key is a puzzle game where you try to obtain a certain key to lock away the evils of the world. There really isn't that much depth to it, but it's got an interesting art style.
title: Evil Key

text: Drip is a game about moving small droplets of water through the soil. There's a few puzzle elements in here, but it's a fairly standard run-of-the-mill mobile game; nothing spectacular, but a decent time waster.
title: Drip

text: This game is entertaining. There's something satisfying about sending little worms into the air with a jet pack. I would recommend this game to people who like physics and jumping games.
title: Jet Worm

text: Faaalling Balls is like Tetris, but with balls. The game tries to make you empathize with these balls, but when you realize the red one is always angry at you, you'll probably just smash em all anyways.
title: Faaalling Balls

text: In this game you're an astronaut going through mazes in space. Entertaining and fun with good graphics. It helps you exercise those problem solving skills!
title: Mazonaut

text: Gum Drop is practically a Candy Crush Saga clone, which was also a Bejeweled clone. There's nothing much to see here; you'll get the general idea if you played any of the other games.
title: Gum Drop

text: Toss the Bird is practically a clone of Angry Bird, but less well done. You'll toss chicks across several different levels with fewer new elements than Angry Birds. You're probably better off playing Angry Birds.
title: Toss The Bird

text: This is another physics based game with crates and an outdoor theme. While they could have picked something more interesting than crates, it seems fun nonetheless.
title: Crate

text: This entertaining game features little sludge monsters. It's fun and doesn't involve normal animals, which get a little boring in games after a while.
title: Waste

text: Brainergy is one of those games that try to expand your intellectual capabilities" through the use of "intellectually boosting games." It's pretty standard stuff but the art style is interesting enough. "
title: Brainergy

text: This game is fun with good graphics. Trying to displace the ball is your goal. It is simple but manages to still be entertaining. It's an easy way to pass time.
title: Knock It

text: This is a simple and entertaining maze game where you are exploring mazes in underground caves. The pixel graphics are nice and reminiscent of old arcade games.
title: Little Caves

text: Animal Eye is a game similar to Angry Birds where you try and aim what the animal is interested in and shoot it. There's nothing too spectacular about this game.
title: Animal Eye

text: Build A Path is a game where you have to guide a lost kid out of the woods by building a path home. It's a puzzle game with some classic elements, but after a few levels, it gets a bit repetitive.
title: Build A Path

text: Enter the Grid is a puzzle game that doesn't stand much outside of other mobile puzzle games. There's not much here other than a few varying puzzle levels, so you can probably save your phone's memory and not download it.
title: Enter The Grid

text: This game is fun for both casual game-players and those with a fascination for science. Entertaining, microscopic game play that makes time pass quickly.
title: Glow Worm

text: This is a fruit physics game. Fight and manipulate the element of gravity to try to help your orange. Entertaining and similar to other gravity games.
title: Gravity Orange

text: This game is simple and elegant and features colorful little dots. Your goal is to get dots of the same color together. It is fun and doesn't try to be overly complicated or quirky.
title: Droppix

text: The goal of Expand It is, well, to expand a little green monster. You'll have to assimilate different monsters to make yours grow larger, so there's not much depth to this game.
title: Expand It

text: Rainbow Ball Rush is a game about filling up the world with color with your oh-so-colorful ball of colors. You'll roll it around the screen and... that's it. It's pretty repetitive.
title: Rainbow Ball Rush

text: Tanglers is a game about matching things in the spirit of Bejeweled. There's not much here to see other than some creepy tentacle monster getting tangled up by matching all these things.
title: Tanglers

text: Catapulten is a bejeweled clone with terrible graphics and a seemingly poor randomization system. It's either too easy or impossible to get combos to move on to the next stage. Look away from this one.
title: Catapulten

text: Hank Hazard is a game about Hank the Space Chipmunk. You'll throw him all across some anti-gravity stages in the same vein as Angry Birds, but with a socially awkward chipmunk.

text: In this game you have to navigate through many levels while trying to make sure that the key combination fits. The artwork for this game was really cool too.

text: This is a basic puzzle game that involves matching. It is a brighter, more intense version of many puzzle games that already exist. I find the bright colors difficult to look at for a long time, and do not like this game.
title: Blink Blox

text: This app gives you hundreds of mazes in order to navigate. It's not anything incredibly special, but I liked it because it has unlimited entertainment for killing time.
title: Mazes

text: This game requires you to direct wood through a logging area. It was pretty boring, a lot like the pipe games where you try to direct water through to the end.
title: Timber Slide

text: In this game, you control a coconut on an island. It is an adventure style game where you avoid obstacles that seems similar to many other adventure games that already exist.
title: Drop The Nut

text: In this game, you must connect pipes using other plumbing tools. It is a puzzle game made realistic because connecting pipes to let water flow through is actually something done in real life. This game is the cartoon version of glorified plumbing, and there is really no point to it.
title: Pipe Fiction

text: In this game, you match shapes into different spaces. It seems very simplistic and similar to the toy that toddlers play with where they put different shaped blocks through different holes.
title: Shape Star

text: In this game you are matching up different characters and more can be revealed throughout the challenge. I thought that the characters looked fun and it kind of reminded me of Mario.
title: Kinopian

text: In this game, a worm has been attached to a jetpack and you must control him as he flies around on an adventure. The graphics are very bizarre, and may appeal to younger kids who like bright colors and exaggerated objects.
title: Jet Worm

text: Cub and Mag are two friends that are separated from each other and you have to try and reunite them. Even though the characters look cute, it didn't seem to be like a game that was particularly challenging.
title: Cub And Mag

text: In this game, you control different owls in the branches of a tree. The graphics are very cartoonish, but in a cute and endearing way. The concept does get boring quickly because the game is always the same.
title: Hoot

text: This game is about a knight that has to navigate through different challenges. I was mostly off put by the icon, the illustration was weird and it distracted from what the game was about.
title: The Quest

text: In this puzzle game, you control frogs and help them move around. The graphics include very bright colors, and this is a simplified puzzle game.
title: Flexy Frogs

text: This game is a live action game, you are trying to solve the puzzles in a race against time. The animation looked cool and I like challenging puzzle games.
title: Non Stop

text: In this tunneling game, you must dig below the earth in a series of mazes. The graphics are very crude and pixelated, and the game seems more like an arcade game than a modern game to be played on a phone or other high-tech device.
title: Little Caves

text: This vampire game is somewhat violent despite its cartoonish graphics. The purpose of the game is to destroy, which seems like it will quickly become boring.
title: Vampire Village

text: Fruit fling is a game that asks you to match up different fruits in order to eliminate them, with the end goal of clearing through the levels. I like games like this a lot so it was fun to play.
title: Fruit Fling

text: This game has you navigate through different levels underground, destroying obstacles and trying to make it through to the end. It didn't seem that interesting to me.
title: Rusty Orb

text: In this game, you match colored circles in order to clear space on the board. It is a classic puzzle game with very basic graphics. It may be fun for a little bit, but this game is unoriginal and seems like it would get boring quickly.
title: Droppix

text: This is a puzzle game that includes a cartoon teddy bear as its main character. It seems boring and very simplistic, and though it may be fun initially it seems like it would get tiresome quickly because of its uninteresting graphics and simple design.
title: Block Bear

text: In this game, you control a character that is trying to escape. The process of escaping involves solving puzzles as well as confronting odd characters. I enjoy escape games, but this one seems rather bizarre and the graphics are unimpressive.
title: Let Me Out

text: In this puzzle, you must move around red blocks in order to free the one neon block. It is very similar to other existing games such as Rush Hour, but the graphics are poor.
title: Red Block Puzzle

text: In this game, you help an astronaut race through a maze. The graphics are beautiful though the concept is simple, and this game seems very fun. It does not matter that the character is an astronaut (the game would be the same if it were anything else), but it is still fun.
title: Mazonaut

text: In this game, you make different Voodoo characters fight against each other. It seems very pointless and crude, and the graphics are unimpressive.
title: Voodoo Friends

text: This game is about aliens in outer space and you're trying to free the tanglers in order to win the puzzles. It didn't seem that interesting to me because it was about aliens.
title: Tanglers

text: In this game you are playing as a demon that is trying to make their way through different levels. I didn't really like this game because of the demon character, he looks like he's a punk.
title: Safire

text: In this game, you control a ball as it avoids obstacles and travels through its adventure. The graphics are almost unpleasant to look at, and I really would not recommend this game.
title: Knock It

text: In this game, help a pig make and eat pastries. This game is very cartoonish and simplistic, and may entertain young kids who laugh at the image of a pig in a chef's hat but definitely will not appeal to a larger audience.
title: Pastry Pig

text: In this game, you help a squirrel collect and store acorns. Not only is it similar to many other adventure style games that already exist, but it is similar to other games involving squirrels and nuts in this sequence. The graphics are especially poor.
title: Little Acorns

text: This game was a puzzle game in which you navigate through many levels of manipulating the lights. The puzzles sounded interesting and the icon looked like it has some cool animation.
title: Lights Off

text: This game has a pretty cool story line. It's all based around a mystery in which you go around a house collecting clues in order to piece together the answer to the mystery.
title: Victorian Mysteries

text: This game is for anyone who loves memory puzzles and mazes. You have to race against time in order to navigate a path previously shown. It's great for those who like a challenge.
title: Wayse

text: Hank is a squirrel that is trying to collect acorns and get through many different challenging obstacles. I thought that I would be willing to try the app because Hank looks cute and it might be fun.
title: Hank Hazard

text: In this game, the goal is to turn all of the tiles the same color. You click on a tile to flip it over, but that also flips over all of the tiles surrounding it. It is a challenging puzzle game but similar to a Rubik's cube; once you figure it out once, it becomes boring to play again.
title: All Out

text: In this game, you try to save all of your prized possessions (including your television) from an impending natural disaster, presumably some kind of huge storm. This is a real world issue that is in no way entertaining as a game, and the poor graphics make it even less appealing.
title: Save My Telly

text: This game requires you to navigate a scene in order to locate animals on a list given to you. It's pretty good for kids, more cute than challenging.
title: Animal Eye

text: This game is a challenging, fast paced puzzle. It has a very simple yet pleasing design, but the game itself is actually very complicated and addicting.
title: Pathway Game

text: This is a fighting game between different robot characters. The intense graphic style and robots seem like they would appeal to younger kids, but did not appeal to me.
title: Droid Getaway

text: To be honest, I don't really remember what this game was actually about. I do remember that it was a pretty generic description and it reminded me of a lot of other maze games that I've seen before, pretty unoriginal.
title: Enter The Grid

text: In this game, you must escape an elaborate castle that is a maze and includes many obstacles. The graphics appear very strange -- a mix between cartoon and realistic -- but the adventure-style game seems fun.
title: Castle Escape

text: In this game, you control a little character driving a car down a road. The graphics are very poor and the concept is uninteresting. I would not play this game.
title: Slide Road

text: In this game your character has to go around and destroy all of the bad atoms. It's a cute concept and science related which I thought was cool. Good for any kids that like science-y things.
title: Atom Crusher

text: In this game there are balls falling through different obstacles and you have to help them navigate their way through. I thought that it was like a lot of other games that I have seen.
title: Faaalling Balls

text: This game requires you to navigate through different challenges, like around bulldozers in order to save your home as an endangered armadillo. I didn't like it because it makes me think of the 'wild west' and that's not really something I'm interested in.
title: Armadillo

text: In this game, you control the character Odum, who is a round ball. It is a classic adventure style game that involves traveling through terrain while avoiding obstacles like spikes. The game is fine but nothing special.
title: Odum

text: In this game, you create a path for the ball as it travels. The graphics are extremely simplistic, and the game doesn't change much as you progress.
title: Deflection

text: Cute orange! Basic game! You'll have fun 'defying gravity' with your fruity friend for an hour or two before you decide to drink a nice glass of OJ instead and move on with your life.
title: Gravity Orange

text: I have absolutely no recollection of this app.  I guess it's about growing things?  With a dinosaur?  I don't think I like this app and I definitely don't like that dinosaur's face.
title: Expand It

text: I think this was about droids that had to be saved.  It didn't seemed that cool, I wasn't interested in the game aspect and the plot seemed sort of boring to me.
title: Rusty Orb

text: Squash various opponents and obstacles as an ill-tempered, over-inflated golf ball. Weird concept but surprisingly fun...at least for the first little while.
title: Knock It

text: This one sounded science-y.  I think it even directly referenced physics.  I didn't like science in school and I don't like it now.  Also the atom looked confused.  I thought atoms were made up of protons and electrons? That just looks like a gooey chicken nugget that's spoiled.
title: Atom Crusher

text: You had to collect logs by directing the flow of water through different slides.  With the logs you could build a cabin.  I assume the more logs you had the better your cabin would be.  I wasn't too interested by the log aspect but the cabin aspect seemed cool.
title: Timber Slide

text: Pretty colours! Fairly average puzzle game where you use a glow worm to navigate through a variety of challenges and obstacles. It's ok at first.
title: Glow Worm

text: Ugh.  You had to build a catapult so that you could get/throw cheese.  Cheese is not cool to throw, a watermelon is cool to throw.  I would play a watermelon launching game but cheese?  Eh.  I gave this one a 1 or a 2.
title: Catapulten

text: Oh this one was cool, it was about escaping from a pyramid or a tomb that you had somehow gotten yourself stuck in.  I think there was a treasure involved as well.  I liked the look of the pyramid.
title: The Pyramid

text: Really fun app! Use your teamwork skills to combine the skills of a bunch of different voodoo characters in order to solve various challenges. Good game to procrastinate with!
title: Voodoo Friends

text: Puzzle game centered around falling boxes. Fun at first but won't keep you coming back forever. Still worth a try if you like fast-paced gameplay.
title: Crate

text: This one seemed cool but I don't remember what it was about.  I think you rode on the space dust to explore places and did puzzles along the way.  That seemed like fun.
title: Space Dust

text: Something about cows.  They weren't the smartest on the barn and you had to organize them.  This was difficult because of the stupid cows.  Sort of mean to cows, don't you think?
title: Moovin Up

text: You create various pathways to move through different settings. Gets difficult later on, but it's decently fun and worth a try if you like mazes and strategizing.
title: Pathway Game

text: This was basically a simon says/maze game.  You had to find a path out of a maze.  I liked it because it seemed straightforward and like something I could do without thinking too much/passively.
title: Find Path

text: It's another average app with a somewhat forgettable premise. Something to do with solving puzzles against the clock. Not highly recommended.
title: Tryptic

text: Similar to Angry Birds. You try to figure out the proper angles and force with which to have your squirrel hurl various nuts at different targets. Decently fun.
title: Nuts Physics

text: You were trying to squash/get rid of the bugs.  There wasn't much else to it.  I'm not even sure if there was a strategy behind it; it seemed like you were just supposed to focus on bug smashing.
title: Bug Battles

text: The balls were falling?  I think this was another app that referenced physics.  You might have had to pick things up with the balls while they fell or catch them.  It didn't seem that fun.
title: Faaalling Balls

text: Help various robots through a variety of obstacles. Decent game to pass away a few hours, but nothing special. Pretty average gameplay and an attempt at a narrative.
title: Trampoloons

text: You basically had to open a safe.  That was it.  I don't know how this could get more difficult or have many levels.  It seems like it would be fun a few times and then boring.
title: Crack That Vault

text: An enjoyable game! You create complex systems of pipes in order to get the water supply necessary to irrigate the farmer's field. A challenging and fun play.
title: Pipe Fiction

text: Fun at first but gets a bit too formulaic after playing for a while. Another grid-style puzzle game but not very engaging or addicting. There's better out there.
title: Blink Blox

text: Not extremely creative. Cute duck but pretty basic gameplay. Good for a few hours then may get a bit dull. Not highly recommended, but not the worst!
title: Agent Duck

text: This was a plot based game that had a lot of different aspects to it.  The little monster seemed less like a character and more like a game aspect so it didn't seem too kiddish/obnoxious.  I remember really liking the description of this one.
title: Box Monsters

text: In this game you launch small insects at various enemies and targets. Can be a bit addicting, but gets old rather quickly. Give it a try if you're a fan of other similar games.
title: Jump Out

text: You had to get rid of the zombie granny.  You were a zombie also if memory serves.  I wasn't really interested in it- it sounded sort of cheesy and overplayed.
title: Zombie Granny

text: This was a maze game that had different levels of mazes to escape.  I liked the idea of it because it looked/seemed really basic.  It seemed like the type of game I could just pick up and play when I was bored but still put back down.
title: Mazes

text: Building on the vampire craze, you solve various puzzles in a town full of vampires. Fun concept, average execution. A decent choice if you're bored.
title: Vampire Village

text: I don't remember this one, I think it was one of the basic ones that was focused around a single task.  It seemed like it could have been fun (or this might have been the one that sounded very dumb- the logo is throwing me off).
title: Enter The Grid

text: This was a game where you threw a bird across something and tried to hit things.  It sounded like angry birds but even less exciting.  I wasn't interested.
title: Toss The Bird

text: You burrow underground and make your way through a series of underground mazes of increasing difficulty. Pretty fun app if you're a fan of maze games.
title: Little Caves

text: Not highly recommended. Help these rascally rabbits commit various heists but find yourself deleting the app shortly after you start playing.
title: Robber Rabbits

text: A bunch of bullies have stolen this cute kitten's delectable olives! Help her get her snacks back in this racing game that will entertain you for a few hours.
title: Slide Road

text: Yawn! A worm has a jetpack strapped on his back by his worm compatriots and you have to help guide him through various obstacles and courses. Not worth the download.
title: Jet Worm

text: There's a secret key that you either have to find or use to escape from a series of mazes and puzzles.  I thought the story of the app seemed interesting and dark.
title: Evil Key

text: Not recommended. Doesn't seem like a lot of time or effort was invested in this puzzle game. Kind of poor design and boring gameplay. Can't really even recall how to play.
title: All Out

text: Ah floobz.  The floobz were the characters you were trying to save or kill.  They seemed really annoying and the story seemed babyish.  Also floobz is a horrible name it sounds like boobs.  And they look like boobs!  Is that on purpose??
title: Floobz

text: This one had more goofy characters that turned me off of it.  Also is that a plume on the knights head?  It was confusing to me at first.  Overall it didn't seem that original or exciting.
title: The Quest

text: I think that Hank was a racer of some kind.  I don't remember many of the details of the app.  I don't recall being very interested by it or drawn in to it.
title: Hank Hazard

text: Help the astronaut protagonist avoid various celestial threats--from comets to aliens--and complete a series of levels of increasing difficulty. Pretty fun.
title: Mazonaut

text: You're either growing plants or cleaning a water supply.  I remember thinking that the app looked boring because it seemed too scientific and without plot.
title: Drip

text: You had to collect tanglers for some reason.  I'm not sure if it was to save them or use them for yourself.  It involved puzzle and plot.  I thought it sounded fun but wasn't too excited by it.
title: Tanglers

text: This one sounded science-y but in a cool way because it was about protecting the environment.  Also there was something about making the sky pretty cool colors and patterns.  I liked the concept.
title: Brainergy

text: Fun puzzle game in which you lead your character to safety through various mazes and traps within a castle. Worth the download, but not amazing.
title: Castle Escape

text: Goofy application about saving your television from various threats: natural disasters, aliens, etc. It's a pretty silly premise and the gameplay isn't much better.
title: Save My Telly

text: You had to match the missing parts to the proper robot.  The game seemed simple and wasn't too captivating besides the puzzle aspect.  I wasn't excited by the robot theme.  It seemed like it could get boring.
title: Rusty Robots

text: This game gets pretty tired pretty quickly. Average combination of puzzles and a cute animal, but not really worth the download. You can find something better.
title: Flexy Frogs

text: Yet another instance of the inexplicable proliferation of squirrel-based puzzle games. This one you race around as a squirrel. Seems hastily designed. Pass.
title: Stash Dash

text: I liked the name of these characters.  You had to do something with them so that they could either run away together or solve puzzles.  It was cute- maybe too cute.
title: Cub And Mag

text: You had to guess a number that was within a certain range with a certain number of guesses.  This seemed cool because it was logic and luck rolled into one and wasn't gimmicky.
title: High Low Spinner

text: Highly recommended. Fun and engaging puzzle game that includes a variety of different challenges and tasks. Gets tricky as you increase in difficulty.
title: Hoot

text: This one seemed odd.  There were mushrooms?  You had to match them I think?  I wasn't impressed by the description and didn't like the faces.
title: Kinopian

text: Decent game, though nothing extremely original. Solve puzzles as your amphibian friend. Good to waste an hour or two but not super addicting.
title: Ancient Frog

text: I didn't like this one.  It sounded like candy crush and had something about matching and gum drops and other fruits.  It seemed lame and lacking a story.
title: Gum Drop

text: Cute game but somewhat unoriginal and repetitive. Solve geometric puzzles and look at a cute bear! Probably won't become your new favourite.
title: Block Bear

text: This game was time dependent and involved wither matching or eliminating tiles.  You had to eliminate them constantly or do something with them constantly.  It seemed like fun.
title: Non Stop

text: This was about a character who was doing something.  I remember he was described as impish or devilish.  It seemed annoying and I didn't like the idea of a troublemaking character.
title: Safire

text: There was a mystery you had to solve using plot clues and puzzles.  It was victorian themed which seemed more mature/interesting.  It seemed complicated in a good way.
title: Victorian Mysteries

text: You had to turn all of the lights off.  It seemed like a cool puzzle and there were clues somehow involved.  I liked the idea of it, it seemed like a game I would play.
title: Lights Off

text: This game has a variety of levels and difficulty modes, from the mind-numbingly simple to the obscenely difficult. A good play for any intense puzzle enthusiasts!
title: Red Block Puzzle

text: Another generic matching game where you group objects together by colour and shape. Not really worth the download as there are superior games with similar premises.
title: Shape Star

text: Pretty average puzzle game. You lead your robot to safety, avoiding any obstacles. Can be a bit repetitive. Decent design. You can probably find a more engrossing game.
title: Droid Getaway

text: Help your cute alien/insect friend escape from various tight spots. Gets a little repetitive, but decently fun at first to kill a few hours.
title: Let Me Out

text: You had to build a path to get home.  It sounded basic.  I was interested in the challenge but didn't know how fun the game could be after a long time.
title: Build A Path

text: You just threw fruit.  That's it.  In real life that sounds like it would be fun to do.  I didn't see the point of it as an app.  Just flickin' virtual fruit around, don't mind me.
title: Fruit Fling

text: Help two mice friends escape a lab that has been conducting experiments on them. It's a quirky premise, but the gameplay is a bit generic. Still fun!
title: Mice Run

text: Not very creative or fun. Complete various puzzles as little blob with an odd facial expression but you'll probably get tired of it pretty quickly.
title: Odum

text: The characters must escape from the monsters on the islands using a series of puzzles, riddles, and action games.  The game is character based and fast paced.
title: Lambi Islands

text: I don't remember a lot about this game but I think here was something about the rainbow ball being a character.  It seemed a little too childish to be captivating.
title: Rainbow Ball Rush

text: A rather forgettable puzzle game where you match different colours together and try to get a better high score. Good app to play if you don't feel like concentrating.
title: Droppix

text: Collect acorns to keep the squirrel protagonist happy and healthy. A little generic and doesn't have great re-play value. Keep looking for something more entertaining.
title: Little Acorns

text: I think this might have been one of the candy crush rip offs where you had to match three of the same things to eliminate them.  I'm not 100% sure.  I wasn't that interested in it.
title: Animal Eye

text: Fun matching game where you have to discern what links three different squares and match them together. Gets trickier as you advance to higher levels and provides an enjoyable challenge.
title: Triples

text: Puzzle game full of slime, goo, and cute sewer critters. Kind of formulaic, but decently enjoyable at first. Don't waste too much time on Waste....ha!
title: Waste

text: A decently fun puzzle game where you fend off various objects as you progress through a colourful linear path. Give it a try if you're bored.
title: Deflection

text: Pretty average game. Use your pig to create various baked goods. Premise gets a bit repetitive after a while and the graphics are a bit off-putting.
title: Pastry Pig

text: Fairly boring and unoriginal game. You drop the nut on various moving targets below and try to get higher scores. There are better apps with similar content.
title: Drop The Nut

text: I did not like this armadillo's face at all.  It was not natural.  Also this game had some silly story behind it about the evil armadillo.  It didn't entice me.
title: Armadillo

text: There was some sort of strategy to getting out of a maze or moving tiles.  I remember it sounding somewhat difficult which was interesting to me.
title: Wayse
